President Donald J. Trump and First Lady Melania Trump hosted a dinner at the White House to honor the White House Historical Association. The event included cocktails in the East Room and a seated dinner in the State Room. Melania Trump delivered a speech, reflecting on her recent trip to Florida with the President and Vice President Pence, and highlighting the resilience of the American people. She also discussed the history of the White House Historical Association, which was founded by First Lady Jackie Kennedy in 1961. Melania Trump thanked the supporters of the association for keeping the stories and artifacts of the White House alive for future generations. Notable artifacts on display at the event included a cane used by President William McKinley when he was shot in 1901 and President Ronald Reagan's personal journal.